# OutsideOfBagrad_a0dc16b8 (line 38520)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_a0dc16b8:
    # "Eager for battle, but scared of heights, she joked to herself."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_dc88924b (line 38521)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_dc88924b:
    # "Suddenly an ear piercing scream rang out and Sarah saw a shadow shift past the ladder."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_6f6740c9 (line 38522)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_6f6740c9:
    # "Looking down, against her own instincts, she saw that the first man up the ladder was now falling down, screaming as he did."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_77131453 (line 38523)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_77131453:
    # "Smoke was rising from his face. But Sarah realized, there wasn't much of a face there, only a pitch black goo that bubbled."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_0a1cdd29 (line 38524)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_0a1cdd29:
    # "Boiling oil, she realized. They were throwing burning oil down at them."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_fde98e9d (line 38525)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_fde98e9d:
    # "Hesitation now meant death."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_3be28320 (line 38526)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_3be28320:
    # s "Up the ladder! Keep moving!"
    s ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_712a1d1b (line 38527)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_712a1d1b:
    # "Sarah screamed and physically pushed her soldiers up the ladder."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_06f4108b (line 38528)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_06f4108b:
    # "Off to the sides, she saw more oil being poured down."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_e68c7ec8 (line 38529)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_e68c7ec8:
    # "Her hands were frantically reaching for the next bar, and the next. Out here, on the ladder, she was too vulnerable."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_be0aa88d (line 38530)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_be0aa88d:
    # "Sarah felt herself run out of breath."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_f8ae770e (line 38531)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_f8ae770e:
    # "All around her, the kinds of screams only burning flesh produced, grew louder."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_dcb3593f (line 38532)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_dcb3593f:
    # "Suddenly, her hand touched the last bar."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_d1a38a79 (line 38533)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_d1a38a79:
    # "As Sarah rose up further, she grabbed the top of the battlements, pulling her body over the edge and all but throwing herself onto the walls of Bagrad."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_2e212c94 (line 38539)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_2e212c94:
    # "Solid ground beneath her feet."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_cb3b464b (line 38540)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_cb3b464b:
    # "All around her, she saw other soldiers scale unto the wall."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_9cd85d3d (line 38541)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_9cd85d3d:
    # "But Sarah could not look at them, for before her, was something that stunned Sarah's imagination."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_116e664a (line 38542)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_116e664a:
    # "From atop the wall, all of Bagrad could be seen. The city stretched out seemingly as far as the horizon, in each direction, fully occupying Sarah's field of view, no matter where she looked."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_d984a5a2 (line 38543)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_d984a5a2:
    # "A city like this, there was none like it in all the world."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_d9a15883 (line 38544)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_d9a15883:
    # "Sarah felt a sadness come over herself. Even in ruins, far past its prime, this city was a jewel like no other."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_f9e9e762 (line 38545)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_f9e9e762:
    # "People had build this, and lived here. All across the city, wonders rose up, and in the center, the greatest of all, a palace that seemed to shame any other in existence."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_ca1e2de2 (line 38546)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_ca1e2de2:
    # "Sarah imagined that the people of this city must laugh if they ever saw anyone call Castle Reinmeer a castle. Compared to this, her ancestral home was a hovel."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_01912636 (line 38547)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_01912636:
    # "The city had fallen from its heights, centuries before Sarah was even born, but now she wished with all her heart that she could have seen what it was like back then."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_50819a8c (line 38548)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_50819a8c:
    # "Could you grieve for something that never was?"
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_12eef2e2 (line 38549)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_12eef2e2:
    # "But then, Sarah felt her heart steel."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_e14a6f47 (line 38550)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_e14a6f47:
    # "She was not a noble princess, visiting the wonders of the world."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_c8c9e365 (line 38551)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_c8c9e365:
    # "She was a soldier, a mercenary, come to put the final stake in the heart of a dying empire."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_536bd7c7 (line 38552)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_536bd7c7:
    # "There were those who build this marvel, Sarah realized, and there were those who would destroy it. She was the latter."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_f615875b (line 38553)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_f615875b:
    # "She had often prayed that her father might look down on her and be proud of who she had become, but now she prayed that he would look away from her. She could not bear the idea of him watching her do this."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_71a5ef7e (line 38554)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_71a5ef7e:
    # "Forgive me father."
    ""

# OutsideOfBagrad_a9e30a4f (line 38555)
translate ru OutsideOfBagrad_a9e30a4f:
    # "Sarah unsheated her sword."
    ""

